==== IgG Subclass Panel

IgG subclass deficiency, particularly IgG3 deficiency, is found in a subset of ME/CFS patients and is clinically actionable: documented subclass deficiency can inform consideration of IVIG supplementation in refractory cases Testing includes IgG1–IgG4 quantification; IgG3 is the primary antiviral subclass and may reflect impaired antiviral immune responses.

